<br>
Well I have a ton of questions about everything. I'd like many point of view.<br>
<br>
1. Adobe Streamline is really tough to use. Does anyone have any tips and how important is Streamline in the profesional world.<br>
<br>
2. What exactly is the point of Adobe illustrator? And are there any good sites to help with Illustrator?<br>
<br>
3. What is a &quot;tablet&quot;?<br>
<br>
4. When &quot;cleaning&quot; your line art in Photoshop, Paintshop pro, etc... Is it best to use the &quot;Curves&quot; option or the &quot;Levels&quot; option. I have not noticed much difference between the two. Do they both serve the same purpose?<br>
<br>
5. What programs are used to create an Anime? <br>
<br>
6. What does CG art stand for?<br>
<br>
7. How important is it to have a up to date scanner?<br>
<br>
8. Is there any &quot;best&quot; way to ink a drawing? I've noticed in basic animes they dont use really use a certain style... they just go over the lines. Is that wrong?<br>
<br>
9. What anime artist job does not require you to work for microsoft or move to Japan?<br>
<br>
Well, Thats all I have right now... But I know I had so much more to ask. I think I'll stop here for now. Thanks in advance! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uretrotorque.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RetroTorque</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/24/02 9:03:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4394.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/solidnate/sig.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dictionary of questions</span><hr size=1> 1. I don't use streamline.<br>
<br>
2. Illustrator is a vector program usually used to make and print logos and graphics at any resolution. It's also used as a lettering program. Some people, including me, use it as a drawing program too. Type in Illustrator Tutorials in google and all sorts of sites about Illustrator will come up. I find that the users manual is the more helpful than any site. There is also the Illustrator 10 Wow book you can find at Borders or Barnes and Noble.<br>
<br>
3. A tablet is kinda like using a pen on paper as a mouse that's aslo pressure sensitive. That's my best explaination for it. I got mine from the good folks here <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.wacom.com">www.wacom.com</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Check out the site and maybe seeing them will explain what a tablet is better than I can.<br>
<br>
4. They both do the same thing. Just pick which ever you like more.<br>
<br>
5. Likely the same stuff we Yanks use to make comics. Illustrator, Photoshop, Painter, FreeHand... Any decent graphics software should do. If you mean Anime as in animation I can't help you. I don't know a whole lot about professional animation. They propably use Adobe premire as part of the process though.<br>
<br>
6. CG usually means computer generated. Here are the board it usually means computer colored. I.E. &quot;anyone want to cg this&quot; means &quot;does anyone want to color this in photoshop/painter/etc..&quot;<br>
<br>
7. As long as it scans decently you don't need to upgrade to a new one. <br>
<br>
8. There's no wrong way to ink. Do what you like best. Dead lines are probably used more in animation/anime because they're easier to do and save time. <br>
<br>
9. I don't know. But there are animation studios here and in other countries too. It may not be japanese anime style but to me animation is animation.  <p>Be well, do good work, and keep in touch. -Writer's Almanac NPR</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ucaptainmeth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Captain Meth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Violent Femme</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/24/02 9:09:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4394.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.methart.com/t_meth1.jpg  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dictionary of questions</span><hr size=1> Uh, let's see...  where to start...<br>
